CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 11, 1954, pg. 24 reads: "Chow Time - The North Side Elks didn't win the pennant, but they are looking forward to 1955 with full stomachs and bright hopes. The team, shown with its manager, Dolphus M. Jones, as it was entertained at 1907 Webster Avenue.  Front row, left to right, are Jones, Jerry Williams, Joe Thomas, Andre Havner, Jack Bishop, Jerry McCrommow, Billie Robinson, Leonard Jackson.  Back row: Eddie Harris, Noel Roach, Ronald Boyden and Fred Myers. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: North Side Elks Little League baseball manager Dolphus M. Jones, standing with team, front row from left: Jerry Williams, Joe Thomas, Andre Havner, Jack Bishop, Jerry McCrommow, Billie Robinson, Leonard Jackson; back row: Eddie Harris, Noel Roach, Ronald Boyden, and Fred Myers, gathered around table with  punch bowl, sandwiches, and deviled eggs outside of 1907 Webster Avenue, Hill District
